|ShortSummary=A hostage-crisis in a Kansas City dry cleaners forces Janet Leclaire, queen of the "lighter side of life" segment, to don a bullet proof vest and interview the disgruntled gunman face to face.  All to the chagrin of I-24's highly visible, more experienced anchor, Bill Dunne, who clashes with Kozyck over whether Janet is qualified for such a dangerous assignment.
|LineColor=
}}
